s, up to and including character death. As they say, a little knowledge is a dangerous thing. It is totally okay to lie IC about what you are if you're caught using a power. All knowledge of other supernaturals discovered IC must be documented in your character thread, and preferably in the character threads of everyone involved.%0a> %0a> While the tone of this may seem quite harsh, with the experiences we had in the past, the Storyteller and Admin team feels that it is best to be open about our limitations and our expectations beforehand, to prevent misunderstandings and bad feelings.%0a> %0a> The crossover policy extends to rulings on cross-venue items - if you're handing a Fetish, Imbued item, Enhanced item, or even a mundanely crafted item to a character in another venue, the STs in the venue of the receiving character has the final say on the rules for that particular item - including crafting rules. Players and STs of both venues are encouraged to cooperate to find a solution that all parties can live with.%0a> >>%3c%3c%0a> %0a> [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a> %0a> %0a> [[#BookPolicy]]%0a> [++'''Book Policy'''++]%0a> %0a> (:toggle id=box3 init=hide button=1:)%0a> >>id=box3 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a> (:include GameRef.BookPolicy:)%0a> >>%3c%3c%0a> %0a> [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a> %0a> [[#PI]]%0a> [++'''Personal Information'''++]%0a> %0a> (:toggle id=box14 init=hide button=1:)%0a> >>id=box14 border='1px solid #999' padding=5px bgcolor=#black%3c%3c%0a> This is all a fairly common sense but since it's become an issue:%0a> %0a> 1) Do not post the personal information of players on this site without their express permission.%0a> %0a> 2) If you do not want your personal information given out, do not provided it on this site.%0a> %0a> 3) In general, speaking as an internet professional, do not post up detailed information about your life on-line and expect blanket privacy.%0a> >>%3c%3c%0a> %0a