this happens, crossover is at the sufferance of the venues one is crossing over into. The Mage STs did not sign up to ST Changeling or Vampire, and may in fact have limited knowledge of those venues. The Werewolf ST may not be interested in dealing with a Geist right now.%0a%3c When that happens, Venue STs can ask that the parent venue STs of the character crossing over deal with it (usually with cooperation between the STs) to deal with rules and setting consequences of crossing over.%0a%3c %0a%3c This is a Case-by-Case situation, just because one person was allowed crossover does not mean another will be. %0a%3c %0a%3c On an IC note, crossover carries risk, and in crossing over, a player is implicitly stating that they acknowledge those risks, up to and including character death. As they say, a little knowledge is a dangerous thing. It is totally okay to lie IC about what you are if you're caught using a power. All knowledge of other supernaturals discovered IC must be documented in your character thread, and preferably in the character threads of everyone involved.%0a%3c %0a%3c While the tone of this may seem quite harsh, with the experiences we had in the past, the Storyteller and Admin team feels that it is best to be open about our limitations and our expectations beforehand, to prevent misunderstandings and bad feelings.%0a%3c %0a%3c The crossover policy extends to rulings on cross-venue items - if you're handing a Fetish, Imbued item, Enhanced item, or even a mundanely crafted item to a character in another venue, the STs in the venue of the receiving character has the final say on the rules for that particular item - including crafting rules. Players and STs of both venues are encouraged to cooperate to find a solution that all parties can live with.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#365776%25[[#top| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#BookPolicy]]%0a%3c [++'''Book Policy'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=box3 init=hide button=1:)%0a%3c >>id=box3 bo